 has become careless and out of control. It lacks vision and focus. Like the NHS, it seems to be over managed and to be pointing in too many directions. It needs to aim at doing less, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:13pt">but doing it more skillfully and enthusiastically. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:13pt">And with less public money.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:13pt">13</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:13pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:13pt">Probably not. Would a 5 yearly review be a possibility? As with parliament, if the governors are making a mess of things, it would be an improvement to be able to make signi</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:13pt">ficant changes every 5 years.</span><br /></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:13pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>